{"1":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.55","c":"إِذَا","d":"āَhdِiʾ","e":"āَhdِiʾ"},{"b":"0.36","h":"1.03","c":"السَّمَاءُ","d":"ُءٓāَmَّslٱ","e":"ُءٓāَmَّslٱ"},{"b":"3.2","h":"3.9","c":"انْشَقَّتْ","d":"ْtَّqَhsnٱ","e":"ْtَّqَhsnٱ"}],"a":{"g":"When the sky has split [open]","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                وكان إبراهيم ابن أدهم رحمه الله إذا سمع أحدا يقرأ إذا السماء انشقت اضطربت أوصاله حتى كان يرتعد\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, when Ibrahim ibn Adham, may God have mercy upon him, would hear someone recite \"When the sky is split apart [idha al-sama'u inshaqqat],\" his limbs [awṣāl] would tremble until he would shake.\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"2":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.2","c":"وَأَذِنَتْ","d":"ْtَnِhdَaʾَw","e":"ْtَnِhdَaʾَw"},{"b":"0.97","h":"1.68","c":"لِرَبِّهَا","d":"āَhِّbَrِl","e":"āَhِّbَrِl"},{"b":"2.1","h":"3.91","c":"وَحُقَّتْ","d":"ْtَّqُḥَw","e":"ْtَّqُḥَw"}],"a":{"g":"And has responded to its Lord and was obligated [to do so]"}},"3":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.2","c":"وَإِذَا","d":"āَhdِiʾَw","e":"āَhdِiʾَw"},{"b":"0.6","h":"1.06","c":"الْأَرْضُ","d":"ُḍْrَaʾْlٱ","e":"ُḍْrَaʾْlٱ"},{"b":"1.4","h":"2.33","c":"مُدَّتْ","d":"ْtَّdُm","e":"ْtَّdُm"}],"a":{"g":"And when the earth has been extended"}},"4":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.25","c":"وَأَلْقَتْ","d":"ْtَqْlَaʾَw","e":"ْtَqْlَaʾَw"},{"b":"1.0","h":"1.8","c":"مَا","d":"āَm","e":"āَm"},{"b":"1.3","h":"2.56","c":"فِيهَا","d":"āَhyِf","e":"āَhyِf"},{"b":"2.2","h":"4.24","c":"وَتَخَلَّتْ","d":"ْtَّlَhkَtَw","e":"ْtَّlَhk